Quantitative Feedback Theory (QFT) involves the information associated with the model uncertainty and the control requirements in a set of simple curves. The technique mentioned above allows for the use of the nominal plant to design the controller. The controller design is called loop shaping, carried out on the Nichols chart. The loop shaping technique adds poles and zeros until the nominal loop lies near its bounds, as is shown in Fig. 12. The Eq. (21) and the theoretical plant are transfer functions considered in the loop shaping sequence, as shown in Fig. 12.21L01(s)=1s2+s\documentclass[12pt]{minimal}
